 service, environment variable, or system property is required; the artifact brings its compile/runtime dependencies transitively and the javac failure is due to 2.2.1 API changes in existing tests, not missing setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment or system property setup is required. The gitexe provider shells out to the default `git` executable, configurable via `${user.home}/.scm/git-settings.xml`, but meaningful tests can avoid external services by covering command-line builders and output consumers with temp directories. When updating the existing tests for 2.2.1, adapt to the new tag API: use `CommandParameters.SignOption` instead of boolean signing arguments, and call `createPushCommandLine` on a `GitTagCommand` instance rather than statically.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Tests that execute real git commits/tags may depend on local `git` availability and repository/user configuration; prefer command construction, parsers, or isolated local temp repositories unless Native Image verification proves more is needed.\",\n    \"The upstream project has test-only helpers such as `maven-scm-provider-gittest`, but they are not needed to fix the observed compile failure or reach meaningful generated coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0ee45e998b40ef39016a2a53f30d688190815143bec3d383e5\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1201, "output": 800, "cacheRead": 32256, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34257, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781158883372, "responseId": "resp_0ee45e998b40ef39016a2a53e41ea8819080bdb47c9a7d7531"}, "toolResults": []}
